    "#Importing data into tensorflow dataset object\n",
    "\n",
    "from tensorflow.keras.preprocessing.image import ImageDataGenerator\n",
    "\n",
    "# Define the image size\n",
    "\n",
    "IMAGE_SIZE = 128\n",
    "\n",
    "# Initialize ImageDataGenerator for training data\n",
    "\n",
    "train_datagen = ImageDataGenerator(\n",
    "        rescale=1./255,\n",
    "    rotation_range=20,\n",
    "    height_shift_range=0.2,\n",
    "    shear_range=0.2,\n",
    "    zoom_range=0.2,\n",
    "    horizontal_flip=True,\n",
    "  \n",
    ")\n",
    "\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",

     "name": "stdout",

      "Found 3352 images belonging to 7 classes.\n",
      "373\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "#augmented data \n",
    "train_generator = train_datagen.flow_from_directory(\n",
    "        'Cars Dataset/train',\n",
    "        target_size=(IMAGE_SIZE,IMAGE_SIZE),\n",
    "        class_mode=\"sparse\",\n",
    "        shuffle=True,\n",
    "        batch_size=9\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "print(len(train_generator))"
   ]

    "cnn.add(tf.keras.layers.MaxPool2D(pool_size=2, strides=2))"
   ]
  },
  {

   "id": "eae9a3d2",

   "outputs": [],

   ]

    "\n",
    "# Calculate additional evaluation metrics\n",
    "\n",
    "# Predict classes for test data\n",
    "test_predictions = np.argmax(cnn.predict(test_generator), axis=-1)\n",
    "\n",
    "# True classes for test data\n",
    "true_classes = test_generator.classes\n",
    "\n",
    "# Calculate evaluation metrics\n",
    "precision = precision_score(true_classes, test_predictions, average='weighted')\n",
    "recall = recall_score(true_classes, test_predictions, average='weighted')\n",
    "f1 = f1_score(true_classes, test_predictions, average='weighted')\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Precision:\", precision)\n",
    "print(\"Recall:\", recall)\n",
    "print(\"F1 Score:\", f1)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot confusion matrix\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8))\n",
    "sns.heatmap(confusion_matrix(true_classes, test_predictions), annot=True, fmt='d', cmap='Blues', cbar=False)\n",
    "plt.title('Confusion Matrix')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Predicted Labels')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('True Labels')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]

    "# PREDICT  THE CAR MODELS"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 19,
   "id": "47762f5d",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Define function named \"predict\" to predict the class of an image\n",
    "\n",
    "def predict(model, img):\n",
    "    img_array = tf.keras.preprocessing.image.img_to_array(images[i])\n",
    "    img_array = tf.expand_dims(img_array, 0)\n",
    "\n",
    "    predictions = model.predict(img_array)\n",
    "\n",
    "    predicted_class = class_names[np.argmax(predictions[0])]\n",
    "    confidence = round(100 * (np.max(predictions[0])), 2)\n",
    "    return predicted_class, confidence"
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "# Results Interpretation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "469d6791",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Interpretation of Performance Metrics:\n",
    "\n",
    "Accuracy: The accuracy of the model on the test set is approximately 72.2%, indicating that the model correctly predicts the class of images about 72.2% of the time.\n",
    "Loss: The test loss is approximately 2.10, which represents the average loss computed during the evaluation of the model on the test dataset.\n",
    "Precision, Recall, and F1-Score: These metrics provide a more detailed understanding of the models\n",
    "performance across different classes. Precision measures the proportion of correctly predicted positive cases out of \n",
    "all predicted positive cases. Recall measures the proportion of correctly predicted positive cases out of all actual \n",
    "positive cases. F1-score is the harmonic mean of precision and recall, providing a balance between the two metrics.\n",
    "\n",
    "Challenges Encountered:\n",
    "\n",
    "Choosing the number of epoch: The number of epochs during training significantly influences the model's performance.\n",
    "Choosing fewer epochs might lead to lower accuracy compared to training for more epochs. Here choosing lesser number of epoch ended up with getting lawer accuracy which was less than 70. \n",
    "\n",
    "Explore misclassified images and identify potential reasons for misclassifications:\n",
    "\n",
    "After going through the similarities among misclassified images , Common reason that i found for the misclassifications is the similarity between classes."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "3ef62e38",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Conclusion and Recommendations"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "3621370d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "In this project, a Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) was trained to classify car images into seven different categories. \n",
    "The CNN model was trained for 35 epochs and achieved a test accuracy of approximately 72.2%. The performance metrics indicated \n",
    "that the model's performance was satisfactory, but there were areas for potential improvement.\n",
    "\n",
    "Model Performance: The CNN model achieved a moderate level of accuracy, indicating that it can effectively distinguish between \n",
    "different car categories to some extent.\n",
    "\n",
